./.title: HTML
./.body:
Coding & Cocktails Session 1:
Introduction to HTML

Overview
Tonight we covered HTML basics and best practices. We’ll put those to use here creating our own web page and begin understanding HTML structure as well as becoming more comfortable using HTML.

project.html.title: Part 1: HTML Page Structure
project.html.body:
Project
HTML provides your website with the underlying structure.  We'll start with a basic HTML structure and continue with adding page content.
Part 1: HTML Page Structure
We'll explore using the Emmet plugin in the Atom text editor that we use as our development environment.  This plugin helps us write our code faster and more efficiently.

Open Atom
Go to the file menu and choose New File
Go to the file menu and choose Save As...
Name the file index.html and save it in your CodingAndCocktails folder
In your index.html file type html:5 and press the tab button on your keyboard.  This should come out looking like the following: 




  
  
  
  Document







Cheers! You just set up the structural foundation of a web page!

part_2_head_section.html.title: Part 2: Head Section
part_2_head_section.html.body:
Part 2: Head Section
The head section contains data telling your browser more information about your page.  As we get farther into the year we'll discover more pieces of information that fit well here but tonight we'll just cover a couple.

Set the title for your page inside the title tags.  This sets what will show on the tab.  If you need some inspiration let's make a Cocktail Lounge site so set your title to YourName's Cocktail Lounge
Save the file
In your file system, navigate to your CodingAndCocktails folder 
Open the index.html file in your Google Chrome browser
You won't see anything exciting on the page itself yet but you should see your title displayed in the page tab.

part_3_body_section_headers.html.title: Part 3: Body Section - Headers
part_3_body_section_headers.html.body:
Part 3: Body Section - Headers
The body section of your HTML contains the visible part of your webpage.  Let's start building out some content!

Use emmet to add the main header of your page using an h1 tag inside the body section. just type h1 then press the tab key. Don't forget to write the text you want displayed between the opening and closing tags!  If you're choosing to build our cocktail lounge you'll want to write out the name of your cocktail lounge here.

Save your file and reload it in Google Chrome.

Tada! We have content! 

Next, Lets add a subtitle.  What tag do you think we might use here? For our cocktail lounge we might use the text "Cocktails with a side of code"

Finally, we'll add three different sections.  We'll want to use an h3 tag here since this is the third most important heading on the page.  We'll want an "About" section a "Menu" section and a "Contact" section.


If you want to read up on header elements check out the documentation from MDN:
Mozilla Developer Network Documentation on heading elements

part_4_body_section_-_paragraphs.html.title: Part 4: Body Section - Paragraphs
part_4_body_section_-_paragraphs.html.body:
Part 4: Body Section - Paragraphs
Most websites have some text on the page. Let's add some to ours!

After the first h3 tag, add a paragraph tag (Hint: That's just a p tag!) Don't forget to use emmet so you don't have to write out all the , > and \.

We'll use emmet to add some text for us for now.  Lorem ipsum text is often used as dummy text in the printing industry to show what the page layout will look like.

Type lorem inside the p tags and push tab.  This will insert some placeholder lorem ipsum text for you. It should look like this: 




Save your html file and refresh in your Google Chrome browser. You should now see something like this:

part_5_body_section_-_images.html.title: Part 5: Body Section - Images
part_5_body_section_-_images.html.body:
Part 5: Body Section - Images
Add an image to your about section to bring some interest to your page.

Navigate to flickr.com

Search for a cocktail image

Change the license filter from "Any License" to "Commercial use allowed"

Choose your favorite image, click on it and click on the download icon in the lower right corner.  You get to choose what size you'd like on your page. 
 

Add an image tag just below the "About" header on your page.  (Don't forget to use emmet to complete your tag for you and fill out the alt attribute!  The alt attribute content gets displayed if your image is not able to be rendered and is used by screenreaders for better accessibility.

part_6_body_section_-_tables.html.title: Part 6: Body Section - Tables
part_6_body_section_-_tables.html.body:
Part 6: Body Section - Tables
Let's add some content to the menu section!  We'll add a menu inside an HTML table. 

Add an HTML table under the "Menu" header. (Don't forget to use emmet to help you write your HTML faster! 
View the documentation for HTML tables on MDN to get your table structured. You'll find examples towards the bottom of the page.
One column should contain the Menu Item and the other column should contain Price

troubleshooting.html.title: Homework: Troubleshooting
troubleshooting.html.body:
Troubleshooting
Troubleshooting Exercises
In order to continue building our coding skills, we need to practice - just like when playing sports or learning a musical instrument. Let’s try some troubleshooting so you can feel more confident coding on your own!

Open a new file in Atom and save it as troubleshooting.html

Paste the following code into the file



    
    Coding & Cocktails Troubleshooting
    


    Exercise 1
    Figure out what is wrong with this HTML.

    Does anyone know why there is no image displayed below this paragraph?

    
    

    
    How does my table look?
    
        
            Winter Sport
            Equipment
        
        
            Skiing
            Skis
            Poles
            Gloves
            Boots
            Hot Chocolate
            Snow
        
        
            Snowboarding
            Snowboard, boots, gloves, etc.
        
        Snowshoing
        Snowshoes
        
            Sledding
            Sled, etc.
        
    

    
    Is this list formatted according to best practices?
    Here is a list:
    1. First item 
    2. Second item 
    3. Third item 

    
    Keep an eye to the best practices in this section.
    Yay for pretty colors!!!

    This is another paragraph. There is a Coding & Cocktails link in this paragraph. I want only this sentence to be bold. Which cocktail is your favorite tonight?  What is your favorite holiday tradition?  Who likes snow & ice?  Is 3 This sentence should be in italics

    
    

  


Save the file and open it in your Google Chrome browser

The first thing to fix is that our image is not displayed underneath the paragraph.  See if you can make the image show up by editing the HTML. 

Remember to refresh the page in Google Chrome to see your changes


The second issue to fix is the table so it has two columns (Sport and Equipent) with several rows of data.

Next, update the list of items to use an HTML ordered list so our webpage has the correct structure

After that, update the HTML headers keeping an eye to our HTML best practices

Finally, when we talked about image tags there was an attribute we mentioned as a good idea to include on images.  Update the image tag to have this attribute.


View Finished Pages: http://kansascitywomenintechnology.github.io/examples/troubleshooting/troubleshooting.html
